               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ​Khulāṣat al-maʻārif by Muḥammad Fāz̤il ibn ʻAbd Allāh</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85089787​ http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85129660" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_995-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>​ On the fundamental beliefs of Islam as interpreted by the Naqshbandi order. The author may be one Muḥammad Fāz̤il ibn ʻAbd Allāh mentioned in the colophon. The work includes many verses by the author himself and others.</p>
                        <p>​ The introduction is missing and the work begins on folio 6, according to the original numbering, with a masnavi on الم.</p>
                        <p>​ ​ff. 159; 19 lines to a page; fair nastaʻliq; copyist: Muḥammad Fāz̤il ibn ʻAbd Allāh; rubrications; early 19th century.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8032">Muḥammad Fāz̤il ibn ʻAbd Allāh</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8032">​ محمد فاضل ابن عبد الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21826">​Khulāṣat al-maʻārif</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21826">​​ خلاصة المعارف</title>
                  </msItem>
